g.text: Block Hash & Blake3 Proof of Work Hash Serialization (DCP0011)
• All integers are serialized in little endian
• All hashes are serialized in their internal byte order (in the
exact order produced by the hash function)
• Note that hashes are often displayed in reverse order
• The Extra Data field is a binary blob and is serialized unaltered
Implementations often treat the first 4 bytes of the Extra Data field as a
separate Nonce field encoded as a little endian unsigned 32-bit integer
for legacy reasons even though it is part of the Extra Data field
